#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an5.132"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.132:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.132:0.2"
msgid "14. Rājavagga "
msgstr "14. Kings "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an5.132:0.3"
msgid "132. Dutiyacakkānuvattanasutta "
msgstr "132. Wielding Power (2nd) "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an5.132:1.1"
msgid "“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgato rañño cakkavattissa jeṭṭho putto pitarā pavattitaṃ cakkaṃ dhammeneva anuppavatteti; "
msgstr "“Mendicants, possessing five factors a wheel-turning monarch’s eldest son continues to wield the power set in motion by his father only in a principled manner. "

msgctxt "an5.132:1.2"
msgid "taṃ hoti cakkaṃ appaṭivattiyaṃ kenaci manussabhūtena paccatthikena pāṇinā. "
msgstr "And this power cannot be undermined by any human enemy. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an5.132:2.1"
msgid "Katamehi pañcahi? "
msgstr "What five? "

msgctxt "an5.132:2.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, rañño cakkavattissa jeṭṭho putto atthaññū ca hoti, dhammaññū ca, mattaññū ca, kālaññū ca, parisaññū ca. "
msgstr "A wheel-turning monarch’s oldest son knows what is right, knows principle, knows moderation, knows the right time, and knows the assembly. "

msgctxt "an5.132:2.3"
msgid "Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi aṅgehi samannāgato rañño cakkavattissa jeṭṭho putto pitarā pavattitaṃ cakkaṃ dhammeneva anuppavatteti; "
msgstr "A wheel-turning monarch’s oldest son who possesses these five factors continues to wield the power set in motion by his father only in a principled manner. "

msgctxt "an5.132:2.4"
msgid "taṃ hoti cakkaṃ appaṭivattiyaṃ kenaci manussabhūtena paccatthikena pāṇinā. "
msgstr "And this power cannot be undermined by any human enemy. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.149, sc3
msgctxt "an5.132:3.1"
msgid "Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato sāriputto tathāgatena anuttaraṃ dhammacakkaṃ pavattitaṃ sammadeva anuppavatteti; "
msgstr "In the same way, possessing five factors Sāriputta rightly keeps rolling the supreme Wheel of Dhamma that was rolled forth by the Realized One. "

msgctxt "an5.132:3.2"
msgid "taṃ hoti cakkaṃ appaṭivattiyaṃ samaṇena vā brāhmaṇena vā devena vā mārena vā brahmunā vā kenaci vā lokasmiṃ. "
msgstr "And that wheel cannot be turned back by any ascetic or brahmin or god or Māra or Brahmā or by anyone in the world. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an5.132:4.1"
msgid "Katamehi pañcahi? "
msgstr "What five? "

msgctxt "an5.132:4.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, sāriputto atthaññū, dhammaññū, mattaññū, kālaññū, parisaññū. "
msgstr "Sāriputta knows what is right, knows principle, knows moderation, knows the right time, and knows the assembly. "

msgctxt "an5.132:4.3"
msgid "Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato sāriputto tathāgatena anuttaraṃ dhammacakkaṃ pavattitaṃ sammadeva anuppavatteti; "
msgstr "Possessing these five factors Sāriputta rightly keeps rolling the supreme Wheel of Dhamma that was rolled forth by the Realized One. "

msgctxt "an5.132:4.4"
msgid "taṃ hoti cakkaṃ appaṭivattiyaṃ samaṇena vā brāhmaṇena vā devena vā mārena vā brahmunā vā kenaci vā lokasmin”ti. "
msgstr "And that wheel cannot be turned back by any ascetic or brahmin or god or Māra or Brahmā or by anyone in the world.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.132:4.5"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ. "
msgstr ""

